            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EEzekiel%20saw%20a%20massive%20valley%20of%20dry%20bones.%20What%20a%20picture%20of%20today's%20Church-disconnected%2C%20dry%2C%20divided%2C%20and%20dead!%20The%20once-powerful%20army%20of%20the%20early%20Church%20has%20disintegrated%20into%20a%20fractured%2C%20feeble%20graveyard%20of%20spiritual%20relics.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENow%20must%20come%20the%20breath%20and%20life%20of%20God!%20Someone%20once%20said%2C%20%22God%20does%20not%20breathe%20on%20anything%20that%20is%20not%20connected.%22%20As%20believers%20in%20the%20Church%20of%20Jesus%20Christ%2C%20we%20must%20come%20back%20into%20relationship%20with%20one%20another%2C%20crossing%20racial%2C%20denominational%2C%20and%20even%20national%20lines%20of%20boundary.%20In%20Ezekiel%2C%20the%20connecting%20together%20of%20the%20dry%20bones%20brought%20muscle%2C%20tendons%2C%20breath%2C%20and%20balance%20back%20to%20the%20body.%20Then%20the%20revived%20body%20stood%20upright%2C%20a%20great%20army%20filled%20with%20the%20Spirit%20of%20God%20(Ezekiel%2037%3A10).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHow%20easy%20it%20is%20for%20the%20Church%20to%20become%20disconnected%20by%20economic%20status%2C%20race%2C%20or%20educational%20level.%20James%20corrected%20the%20believers%20who%20were%20favoring%20the%20rich%20over%20the%20poor%20in%20their%20congregational%20seating%20arrangements%20(James%202%3A3).%20The%20%22royal%20law%22%20tells%20us%20to%20love%20our%20neighbor%20as%20ourselves%20(Matthew%2019%3A19)%3B%20thus%2C%20the%20Church%20must%20provide%20for%20the%20daily%20physical%20and%20emotional%20needs%20of%20others.%20There%20can%20be%20no%20favoritism%20in%20extending%20the%20love%20of%20Christ%20to%20one%20group%20of%20people%20over%20another.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYou%20cannot%20live%20disconnected%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Body%20of%20Christ.%20Look%20around%2C%20hook%20up%2C%20get%20involved%2C%20and%20feel%20the%20precious%20breath%20of%20God%20invigorating%20and%20empowering%20you!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
